The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, June 2: Increase in prices of basic essential items like vegetables, fruits, milk, tea, chicken, fish-marine and minerals like iron ore pushed up the inflation rate to 4.74 per cent for the week ended May 20. The wholesale price-based inflation rose by 0.42 per cent from the previous weeks 4.32 per cent, but it was still lower than the price rise of 5.38 per cent in the year-ago period, according to the data released by the government.

 Mumbai, June 2: Indias forex reserves declined by $370 million to stand at $162.6 billion during the week ended May 26 against $162.9 billion during the week ended May 19. The reserves had declined by $793 million during the week ended May 12 compared with a week ago.

 New Delhi, June 2: The government has dereserved 180 items in the small-scale sector, including 77 mechanical, 68 chemical and 35 auto component products.

 New Delhi, June 2: Indian Bank is planning to tap the capital market with an initial public offer of 6-8 crore shares early next year, which will dilute the governments holding in the bank.

 New Delhi, June 2: A tax tribunal has ruled in favour of Hero Honda Motors in a case filed by the excise department for alleged duty evasion to the tune of Rs 2 crore.




